        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-59117ea0-cc1f-4387-98dc-ffc473ebcc50">
                Major Haughton  (Antrim)
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-59117ea0-cc1f-4387-98dc-ffc473ebcc50" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1947-05-06/debates/bbb66728-34ae-4ca3-9fde-fb4aa0cb4fcc/Clause1%E2%80%94(LiabilityToBeCalledUpForService)#contribution-59117ea0-cc1f-4387-98dc-ffc473ebcc50">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">I am very sorry, with reference to what my hon., and indeed, my lovable, Friend the Member for Fermanagh and Tyrone (Mr. Mulvey) said, that I cannot claim the distinction of having a V.C. However, I want to say one or two simple things. I have never been accused in the House of Commons of making a long speech, and the one I am about to make will, probably, be the shortest of all. I do not think we need delve back into history. As part of the United Kingdom, we in Northern Ireland claim the privileges and the very great credit that come from being part of the United Kingdom and of the Empire; and, on the other hand, we claim the right to bear the responsibilities of being part of the United Kingdom. As was shown by the tremendous vote in the Lobbies less than an hour ago, Scotland wants to take her full part in whatever the responsibility may be. This matter has been debated in this House in its various aspects, including the terms <span id="309" class="column-number" data-column-number="309"></span> of service, and I think that Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland, too. recognise that each is a part of the United Kingdom. All we are saying in this Committee tonight is that we want to be part of that United Kingdom, both in its benefits and its responsibilities.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-59117ea0-cc1f-4387-98dc-ffc473ebcc50" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1947-05-06/debates/bbb66728-34ae-4ca3-9fde-fb4aa0cb4fcc/Clause1%E2%80%94(LiabilityToBeCalledUpForService)#contribution-59117ea0-cc1f-4387-98dc-ffc473ebcc50">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
