<p class="">I am very sorry, the 12th July celebrates the Battle of the Boyne. [HON. MEMBERS: "When?"] Perhaps hon. Members will allow me to complete the quotation. [HON. MEMBERS: "What year?"] It will come. Hon. Gentlemen opposite should realise that in one particular we are in some difficulty about obtaining information regarding Northern Ireland. It is not one of the courtesies which the Parliament of Northern Ireland extends to this House to send them with any promptitude an account of its proceedings. It was 22 years before they sent to the Library of this House a copy of their regulations under their Civil Authorities (Special Powers) Act.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
