<p class="">On a point of Order. It seems to me that these Amendments, or at least the speeches in support of them, constitute an abuse of the Privileges of Parliament. If hon. Members who support the Amendments are against national service, and believe we should rely upon voluntary service, they should oppose this Bill at the appropriate stages. On the other hand, they have accepted national service for this land, but think a particular part of this land should be exempted.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
